
{center}
{subhead} StarGate 1.1 released{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

Toysoft Development Inc. is pleased to announce the release of StarGate v1.1
e-mail client for the Amiga computers.
{p} {p}
StarGate includes many basic email features such as message attachment and
message decoding. StarGate comes with a very extensive and detailed address
book that supports multiple email accounts, personal and business addresses.
{p} {p}
StarGate 1.1 Features
{p} {p}
-  Multiple mailboxes. (Inbox, Draft, Outbox, Sentbox, Trashcan){p}
-  Unlimited user folders.  Can file message from folder to folder.{p}
-  File messages to other Folders for archiving.{p}
-  Mail sorting. (7 different sorts){p}
-  Custom formating for mailbox and folder columns.{p}
-  Supports multiple E-mail accounts.  Accounts can be turned off at anytime.{p}
-  Detailed address book with multiple email account support.{p}
-  When sending email you can address users by their first or last name.{p}
-  Auto preview of messages even in Mail Peek!!{p}
-  Multiple signatures.  Up to 255 characters long.{p}
-  Unlimited tags. Tags can be upto 255 characters long.{p}
-  Forms in colors and with sounds.{p}
-  Filters for spam mail.  You can Delete, File or Notify with multiple level filters.{p}
-  Multiple mail notification methods. (Sound, dialog box and filter report){p}
-  Peek mail.  Preview your mail on the mail server before downloading.{p}
-  Support PowerPC for MIME decoding and encoding of files.{p}
-  Direct http links to your web browser.{p}
-  Easy file attachments using UU or MIME methods.{p}
-  Helper files to support MIME messages.{p}
-  Check mail on StartUp or on Quit.{p}
-  Button, Large or Small 256 color icon interface.{p}
-  And many more...
{p} {p}
